column1: Week Ending date: the Saturday date for the week in which a claimant is filing for unemployment. The Unemployment Insurance benefit week runs from Sunday to Saturday.

Initial Claim: A notice of Unemployment filed by an individual to request a determination of eligibility for Unemployment Insurance benefits or to begin a second or subsequent period of eligibility within a benefit year or period of eligibility
Source: Nebraska Department of Labor, UI Reports Program

Counts include: New Intrastate initial claims excluding transitional initial claims; additonal intrastate initial claims; interstate taken as agent state initial claims and  Interstate recevied as liable state initial claims

SOC: Standard Occupational Classification, the federal statistical standard used by federal agencies to classify workers into occupational categories for the purpose of collecting, calculating, or disseminating data
Occupational classifications and details can be viewed at https://www.onetonline.org/
Industry Sectors: employers are classified using North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) codes. Claims are provided by major industry sector
Details about industries can be viewed at https://data.bls.gov/cew/apps/bls_naics/v2/bls_naics_app.htm
Race, Ethnicity, Gender and Age: Data categories come from the ETA 203 Report.
Source: Nebraska Department of Labor, Labor Market Informiaton, UI Reports Program, Program to Measure Insured Unemployment Statistics (PROMIS) file
